postcontent:
Trying to sell this one locally first, since I've never gone through the process of shipping a rifle and going through and FFL and whatnot. I'm located in Brockport, but can drive anywhere in the area if needed.

This 1918 BSA Lee Enfield No 1 Mk III* with an Arabic stock disk and rack number on the stock. This rifle has alot of honest looking use from years of history serving somewhere in the Britishicon empire. This is one of the models that was upgraded after World War I with the magazine cutoff (which was cut from production during the war), hence the "*" added to the rifle.

No import mark on this one, so it's probably an older import (or was just luck and missed the mark, ha!).

Also has a very nice bore, with good lands and grooves and general brightness to the whole thing. This and the Arabic history were my two reasons for buying this on a whim several months ago. Only problem this rifle has is a crack on the left side of the stock near the receiver, which I've looked at and determined can be fixed relatively easily. Since I haven't shot it yet, I just never got around to it, ha!

Asking only what I have in it, which is $300. It's hard to find decent Lee Enfields these days since those imports seem to have dried up. I wouldn't be selling this if I didn't have too, but there's a particular rifle I'm buying that is one that is very important to me and that I missed the opportunity to buy several years ago.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom S&W SW99 45 ACP 3 mags XS Big Dot night sights
location: West Central Indiana, Indiana, United States
postcontent: This pistol has had extensive custom work done to it. The grip and back strap, If you've ever handled one of these SW99's feels like a bar of soap. Even with the thin back strap they have a large hump. The hump was shaved and the back strap lines blended. The grip texture is like a medium to coarse grit sandpaper. The grip texture is very pleasant even after several rounds. The grip was shaped to simulate a 1911 with an arched mainspring housing. It has a Bedair custom built stainless captured guide rod and will include the stock polymer rod. XS Big Dot night sights tops off the package (XS is now used by the US Navy Seals) and comes with 3 factory 9 round magazines, factory box, sights and literature. Also in the deal is a new Aker high ride black leather right hand paddle holster. The SW99 series pistol have a very unique trigger system. You can carry the first round as double action. Or in the long single action, or in the short single action, and at anytime there is a de-cocker located on top of the slide. The de-cocker is very easy to operated with either hand and the magazine release is also ambidextrous and very much like the H&K USP's mounted on both sides at the rear of the trigger guard. I like using my right index finger to operate the mag release and my off hand thumb to operate the de-cocker. The pistol also incorporates a firing pin block that is only released at the full depression of the trigger. S&W is the manufacturer of the slide & barrels and Walther is the maker of the frames on the S&W SW99 series pistols. To date S&W is the only company to manufacture this pistol design in the 45 ACP. Currently Walther & Magnum Research are still manufacturing these in 9mm & .40 S&W only.
